args: First I encounter a talking book, and then\nsaid talking book somehow transports me\n40 years into the past?!
Easy, sister! Take a deep breath\nor three and just relaaaax.
*huff* *puff* Yes, that is a bit better.\nNow then, who ARE you?
Me? I'm Douleurâ€”the coolest damn\nmagic diary around!
Yep! See, you've been transported inside\nsomeone's diary...with the power of\nMAAAAAGIC!
So this is the past, but only sorta.\nMore like I gave life to the words\nsomebody scribbled down on paper.
This is somewhat difficult to believe.
Muah ha ha ha! You're one'a them types\nthat needs proof, eh? Well, in that case,\nfeast your eyes on THIS!
Ah! My hand passed right through her!
That's 'cause she ain't realâ€”it's actually\nthe Cassandra from 40 years ago.\nNOW do you believe this is an illusion?
Supposing it is true, whose diary are you,\nand what is your aim in bringing me here?
You really need to ask that first one?\nC'mon, you already know!
I suppose I did suspect as much.
And as for the second question,\nI ain't tryin' to achieve a thing.
I'm just a tour guide for folks that open\nup the diary. Nothin' more, nothin' less.
ï¼‚Day 25, Month of the Stardragon\nThe world has Dragonyule fever!ï¼‚
Ah! I just heard a voice in my head!
Those are the words written in this diary.\nThey're bein' sent directly into your mind.\nLike I said...MAAAAAAAGIC!
ï¼‚This is a day when everyone sets aside their\nworldly cares for pleasureâ€”with one exception.ï¼‚
Oh, you know itâ€”that's King Aurelius!\nEr, the one from 40 years ago, though.
Time for us to witness a little scene\nfrom our dear old Cassandra's past.\nQuiet on the set! Aaaand...ACTION!
You look like you're going to stare a hole\ninto those, Aurelius.
That's quite the pile of documents and\nletters from the people you have there.
You know it's Dragonyule, right?\nNo one would blame you for putting\npaperwork aside and having a bit of fun.
A holiday is no excuse to stop working\nfor my people and country.
Oh, you ARE a model kingâ€”so much so\nthat I can't help but worry about you!
Maybe your big sister should teach you\nsome bad habits so you learn to get out\nand let your hair down! Hee hee!
I think not. Stop treating me like a\nlittle brother.

Someone has hit their rebellious teens!
And I remember when you used to go
on and on about how much you adored
your big sister, the brilliant sorceress.
That was a long time ago.
But since you brought it up, I have long\nthought your lack of temperance to be\ninappropriate for a court sorceress.

That fact is particularly apparent in your
choice of dress, which many of my vassals
have stated they find most improper.
Could you not wear something else?
I live the life I want to live, and that\nincludes my ï¼‚choice of dress.ï¼‚
Still, what a bunch of adolescents we have\nin court if THIS distracts them.
You wouldn't be one of them, mmm?\nMmmmmm?

*sigh* Stop rubbing up against meâ€”
and don't even THINK about doing that
to any of my vassals. You'd likely cause
the poor things to faint dead away.
Enough of this foolishness.\nI have work to do.
Oh, very well. Get to it, then.
Er, do you think you'll get through that\nentire pile before the end of the day?
Because I heard about a delightful little\ncafe that recently opened up in town.
Their Saint Lotier seafood soup\nis supposed to be divine.
Perhaps we could sneak down there\ntogether after you're done with...all this.
You know? Just the two of us?
Hmm? Oh, sorry. I was lost in thought.\nWhat did you just say?
...Never mind. I'll leave you to your work.
ï¼‚When it comes to his people, Aurelius spares\nno effort. He is truly a model king.ï¼‚
That was her memory from 40 years ago.
I had no idea she was so close to His\nMajesty. Their relationship felt more\nlike friends than king and subject.
Yeah, she'd been with him as a court\nsorceress since he was young.
So he saw her as a kind of big sister,\ndespite what he claimed.
Although it appears she thought of him\nin quite a different way entirely.
I suppose it's more of a feeling\nthan anything.
Woman's intuition, eh? Well, let's put\nthose instincts of yours to the test, sister!
We're skippin' ahead a few years!\nMuah ha ha ha!
